      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JALAPENO POPPER (3) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing sixth (24.34) in a Grade 4 at this track. Form here at the trip sound including two wins. The form from her last run stacks up well. Looks the one to beat on her best form. APOLLO'S SUN (2) drew the inside and won last time at this track and distance (24.05), scoring by a nose. Should be in this for a long way. MISS SENORITA (1) stalked the lead and fought on well to finish 7 lengths away in third (24.33) at this track in a Grade 4/5 over 407m. Has performed well from this box with a win and seven minor placings to her name from nine starts. Expected to be in the finish again. CLEAR BLUE SKY (7) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.",
